name: Harbin Ice and Snow World
description: Harbin Ice and Snow World, is a unique ice and snow cultural and tourism festival. It has become the most popular winter attraction in the world. In this dreamy theme park, you can not only see the amazing and colorful illuminated snow and ice sculptures, but also enjoy various interesting cultural activities and winter sports.

name: Sun Island Scenic Area
description: It is best known as the snow sculpture competition and exhibition area of the Harbin International Snow and Ice Sculpture Festival.The island is the site of many square miles of gigantic snow sculptures.These 3-D images are gigantic. In 2007, a 250-meter-long became the world record holder for the largest snow sculpture.

name: Garden By The Bay
description: Beyond the flora and fauna you'll find here, admire the iconic structures of the Gardens: architectural wonders that reinvent nature with artistic finesse.

name: S.E.A. Aquarium
description: Aquarium is one of the world’s largest aquariums, home to more than 100,000 marine animals representing 1,000 species across more than 40 diverse habitats. The vast array of aquatic life is complemented by interactive programmes, up-close animal encounters and immersive learning journeys to inspire visitors to protect the world’s oceans.

name: Tanah Lot
description: The Tanah Lot temple was built and has been a part of Balinese mythology for centuries. The temple is one of seven sea temples around the Balinese coast. Each of the sea temples was established within eyesight of the next to form a chain along the south-western coast. In addition to Balinese mythology, the temple was significantly influenced by Hinduism.

name: Nusa Penida
description: The beautiful, exotic Nusa Penida island lies just 25 kilometers from Bali, the most famous tourist destination in Indonesia , Nusa Penida is a much smaller island than Bali, but it has some of the most amazing scenery in the entire Bali province.

name: Bagan in hot air balloon
description: Get the best views of Bagan's 8,000 temples and pagodas, all of which are almost impossible to visit on foot, during a special hot air balloon flight. Taking a flight in the morning means that you will be able to watch the sunrise and see the area at its most magical, when the morning mist covers the vegetation.

name: Izza Gawna Pogoda
description: The wonders of Bagan shine especially brightly when the sun goes down. Seeing the sunset in this plain dotted with temples, which rise above a red earth and seem hidden among the tropical vegetation, is to witness a prodigious spectacle, one of the most beautiful sunsets in the world.

name: Anna Frank House
description: The Anne Frank House (Dutch: Anne Frank Huis) is a writer's house and biographical museum dedicated to Jewish wartime diarist Anne Frank. The museum opened on 3 May 1960. It preserves the hiding place, has a permanent exhibition on the life and times of Anne Frank, and has an exhibition space about all forms of persecution and discrimination.

name: Witch walk
description: Discover the charming city of Bruges with a fun excursion! This fairytale city is one of the most emblematic enclaves of the UNESCO World Heritage. The tour will take you on a guided walk through the charming historic center, with its beautiful canals, ancient cobblestone streets and impressive medieval architecture. During the tour of Bruges, you will also have time to enjoy yourself and be able to go shopping or try its famous beers and chocolates.

name: Franz Joseph Glacier
description: Fran Josef Glacier stretches for 12 km and is located in the protected territory of Westland National Park, on the west coast of the South Island of New Zealand. Together with the Fox Glacier, they are the two most important glaciers in New Zealand and can be visited on the same day. They are surrounded, in part, by a park that is a World Heritage Site: Te Wahipounamu.

name: Milford Track
description: Arguably New Zealand’s most famous walk, the 53 kilometre journey begins at the head of Lake Te Anau, and leads you across suspension bridges, board walks and a mountain pass,The Milford Track will show you pristine lakes, sky-scraping mountain peaks and enormous valley views. It will take you to feel the misty breath of Sutherland Falls, the tallest waterfall in New Zealand.
